BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Standard form is [`Ax+By=C\text{.}`] We need to move [`x`]\- and [`y`]-terms to the same side of the equal sign.

[```\newcommand{\subtractright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}-#1}}}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
[$left0]\amp=[$right0]\\
[$left0]\subtractright{[$b]x}\amp=[$right0]\subtractright{[$b]x}\\
[$s1]\amp=[$c]\\
(-1)([$s1])\amp=(-1)([$c])\\
[$s2]\amp=[$nC]
\end{aligned}
```]

Note that [`[$s1]=[$c]`] is already in standard form, but it's preferable to make the leading coefficient positive.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

